{"lemma":"غَضْبانُ","slug":"غَضْبانُ","root":"غ.ض.ب","root_slug":"غ-ض-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ض-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَضْبان","root":"غضب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31956"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%92%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"angry, furious, enraged","examples":[{"text":"وَلَمَّا رَجَعَ مُوسَى إِلَى قَوْمِهِ غَضْبَانَ أَسِفًا قَالَ بِئْسَمَا خَلَفْتُمُونِي مِنْ بَعْدِي"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣadˤ.baːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31956","headword_ar":"غَضْبَانُ","root":"gDb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) [and, in the dial. of BenooAsad, as is implied by the fem. in that dial. mentioned in what follows,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDobaAnN","text_ar":"غَضْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDibN","text_ar":"غَضِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDuwbN","text_ar":"غَضُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is both masc. and fem.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guDub~N","text_ar":"غُضُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guDub~apN","text_ar":"غُضُبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDub~apN","text_ar":"غَضُبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDab~apN","text_ar":"غَضَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the last, accord. to MF, is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guDabapN","text_ar":"غُضَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) are epithets applied to an angry man: (K:) [the first seems often to signify simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Angry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDibN","text_ar":"غَضِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but accord. to SM,] all these epithets signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soon, angry"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guDub~apN","text_ar":"غُضُبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said in the S to signify, on the authority of As]: (TA:) the fem. of the first word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDobaY","text_ar":"غَضْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and (in the dial. of Benoo-Asad, S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDobaAnapN","text_ar":"غَضْبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) which is seldom used; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDuwbN","text_ar":"غَضُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a fem. epithet [as stated above], (K,) and has an intensive signification: (TA:) pl. (of the first word, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giDaAbN","text_ar":"غِضَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and (likewise of the first)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDobaY","text_ar":"غَضْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guDaAbaY","text_ar":"غُضَابَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDaAbaY","text_ar":"غَضَابَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}